    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2601.00325v1</id>
    <title>KMT-2024-BLG-0816/OGLE-2024-BLG-0519 -- A Microlensing Event with Candidate Free-Floating Planet Lens and Blended Light</title>
    <updated>2026-01-01T12:38:14Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.00325v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.00325v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>We present the discovery of a free-floating planet microlensing event KMT-2024-BLG-0816. The event shows finite-source effect, significant blending light, and no microlensing signal from a putative planet host. Among the free-floating planet events with finite source effects, this is the only event with unresolved blending light. We discuss how follow-up observations can be used to determine whether the blending light originates from a putative planet host.</summary>
